-- ABC-Mart, Alconix, Focus Systems, Meidensha, Tosei Corp.: Japanese Stocks
-- Norie Kuboyama
-- 2010-07-06T00:44:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-06/abc-mart-alconix-focus-systems-meidensha-tosei-corp-japanese-stocks.html

          
          
             Japan’s  Nikkei 225 Stock Average  fell
156.11, or 1.7 percent, to 9,110.67 as of 9:30 a.m. in Tokyo.
The following are among the most active shares in the Japanese
 market  today. Stock symbols are in parentheses after company
names.  
 ABC-Mart Inc.  (2670 JT) declined 3.1 percent to 3,265 yen.
The shoe retailer said same-store sales in June dropped 1.5
percent from a year earlier, dragged down by per-customer sales
which plunged by 6.9 percent.  
 Alconix Corp. (3036 JT) jumped 8.8 percent to 3,030 yen,
headed for the steepest advance since Nov. 26. The maker of non-
ferrous metal products said it will conduct a 2-for-1 stock
split.  
 Focus Systems Corp. (4662 JQ) surged 17 percent to 260 yen,
headed for the biggest gain since March 2002. The computer-
software developer said it will buy back as much as 2.9 percent
of its shares.  
 Meidensha Corp.  (6508 JT) slumped 3.6 percent to 295 yen,
set for the lowest close since May 2009. The electrical
machinery maker’s stock price estimate for 12 months was lowered
to 300 yen from 450 yen by  Yukihiko Shimada , Mitsubishi UFJ
Morgan Stanley Securities Co., who maintained a “market
perform” rating on Meidensha.  
 Tosei Corp.  (8923 JT) tumbled 7.2 percent to 29,700 yen.
The property developer said first-half net income fell 28
percent to 948 million yen on a 32 percent drop in sales.  
